    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-28T22:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-28T22:36:00-05:00" n="1012"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1012">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.728/2.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-28T21:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 28, 1912—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s March 28, 2 p.m. I have protested verbally, but can not do so
                    effectively because have no direct evidence. Government says consular reports
                    are refused only when line is burdened with official business. Will protest when
                    have positive evidence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
